# Local business-specific sensitive patterns
#
# Copy this file to ~/.claude/sensitive-patterns.local and add your
# organization's identifiers that should never end up in any git repo.
#
# Format: DESCRIPTION|REGEX (pipe-separated, one per line)
# Lines starting with # are comments.
# Empty lines are ignored.
#
# This file is referenced by hooks/pre-push-scan.sh at push time.
# It is NEVER committed — keep it strictly local.
#
# Examples (replace with your actual identifiers):
#
# Supabase project ID (prod)|abc123def456ghi789jk
# Supabase project ID (staging)|xyz789qrs456tuv123wx
# Internal API endpoint|api.mycompany-internal.com
# Database host|db.mycompany-internal.com
# Internal email domain|@internal.mycompany.com
#
# Remember:
# - These patterns will be scanned against every file you try to push
# - Matches BLOCK the push (overridable with --no-verify)
# - Don't put actual credentials here — put those in your .env files instead
# - This file catches infrastructure identifiers that shouldn't leak
